  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Physical Security and Stockpile Management and Weapons and Ammunition Destruction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to improve human security in the DRC through the destruction of obsolete and surplus arms and ammunition and through improved management of ammunition depots.  The threat of unsecured and surplus weapons and ammunition in the DRC poses a significant humanitarian and security threat to the country, runs the risk of unplanned explosions at munitions stores, and allows for unauthorized access to weapons and ammunition storage facilities, which contributes to weapons and arms trafficking and fuels armed violence. This project will secure and destroy surplus and unsecure arms and ammunition and will partner with the national police and security forces to build their capacity to manage this threat.</narrative>
  </description>
